 <!-- The Hook -->
 <div class="bg-brandBlue/5 border-l-4 border-brandOrange p-6 rounded-r-xl mb-6 mt-8 speakable">
 <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">Starting a charging accessories brand? One of the most critical decisions you'll face is choosing between <strong>OEM</strong> (Original Equipment Manufacturing, you provide the design, the factory builds it) and <strong>ODM</strong> (Original Design Manufacturing, the factory provides ready-made designs you brand as your own). Your choice determines your supply chain efficiency, time-to-market, and ROI.</p>

 <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed"><strong>Quick answer:</strong> Choose ODM if you are a startup with limited budget (under $20K) and need fast market entry with MOQ as low as 200-500 units. Choose OEM if you have proprietary technology, a larger budget ($50K+), and need complete design control. A hybrid approach works well for mid-range budgets between $20K-$50K.</p>
 </div>

