 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">1. OEM vs ODM: At-a-Glance Comparison for B2B Buyers</h2>

 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">OEM means you own the design, the factory executes your specs. ODM means the factory owns a proven design, you brand and sell it. For procurement teams, the decision comes down to <strong>budget, timeline, IP control, and product differentiation</strong>. Here is the full comparison:</p>

