 <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-6">
 <h4 class="font-black text-blue-700 uppercase mb-3"><svg class="icon-rocket mr-2" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" viewBox="0 0 512 512">
 <path d="M128 320L24.5 320c-24.9 0-40.2-27.1-27.4-48.5L50 183.3C58.7 168.8 74.3 160 91.2 160l95 0c76.1-128.9 189.6-135.4 265.5-124.3 12.8 1.9 22.8 11.9 24.6 24.6 11.1 75.9 4.6 189.4-124.3 265.5l0 95c0 16.9-8.8 32.5-23.3 41.2l-88.2 52.9c-21.3 12.8-48.5-2.6-48.5-27.4L192 384c0-35.3-28.7-64-64-64l-.1 0zM400 160a48 48 0 1 0 -96 0 48 48 0 1 0 96 0z" fill="currentColor"/>
 </svg>When to Use Hybrid</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Hybrid is ideal when: you have a unique selling proposition that can be implemented with targeted tooling; you want to test market response before full OEM investment; you need to differentiate from competitors using similar ODM products; or your target MOQ falls between typical ODM and OEM ranges.</p>
 </div>

 <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-slate-900 uppercase italic mb-6 mt-10">What About OBM? When You Outgrow OEM</h3>
 <div class="bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-xl p-6 mb-4">
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-3"><strong>OBM (Original Brand Manufacturing)</strong> is the next step beyond OEM: the factory designs, manufactures, AND markets under its own brand. Most charger brands operate as OEM or ODM clients of factories like WOWOHCOOL, they do not become OBM unless they own the entire value chain (R&D, production, distribution, marketing).</p>
 <ul class="text-slate-600 text-sm space-y-2 mb-3">
 <li><strong>OEM client:</strong> you own the brand and design; factory manufactures.</li>
 <li><strong>ODM client:</strong> you own the brand; factory designs and manufactures.</li>
 <li><strong>OBM:</strong> you own the brand, design, manufacturing, AND distribution.</li>
 </ul>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">If you reach OBM scale, your tooling spend, certification portfolio, and supplier network will look more like ours, typically requiring 50+ R&D engineers and 5,000㎡+ of dedicated production floor. For most brands, OEM with WOWOHCOOL as the manufacturing partner is the optimal end state.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Timeline Comparison -->
 <section id="timeline" class="mb-16">
 <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
 <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">5. How Long Does OEM vs ODM Production Take? (Detailed Timeline)</h2>

 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Understanding production timelines helps you plan launches, marketing campaigns, and inventory. Here's a detailed breakdown for a wireless charger project.</p>
 
 <div class="relative">
 <div class="absolute left-8 top-0 bottom-0 w-0.5 bg-slate-200 hidden md:block"></div>
 
 <div class="space-y-8">
 <div class="relative pl-14 md:pl-20">
 <div class="absolute left-0 md:left-4 top-0 w-10 h-10 md:w-8 md:h-8 bg-brandBlue rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-black text-base md:text-sm z-10">1</div>
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 pl-12 md:pl-0">Week 1-2: Initial Consultation</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">Both models: Requirements gathering, product specifications review, factory assessment, NNN signing</p>
 <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 md:gap-4 mt-2 text-xs">
 <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-brandBlue text-white rounded">OEM: Same</span>
 <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-brandOrange text-white rounded">ODM: Same</span>
 </div>
 </div>
 
 <div class="relative pl-14 md:pl-20">
 <div class="absolute left-0 md:left-4 top-0 w-10 h-10 md:w-8 md:h-8 bg-brandBlue rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-black text-base md:text-sm z-10">2</div>
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 pl-12 md:pl-0">Week 2-4: Design & Tooling (OEM)</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">OEM: 2D/3D design finalization, mold creation, PCBA development</p>
 <p class="text-brandOrange text-sm mt-1 font-semibold">ODM: Skip to step 4</p>
 </div>
 
 <div class="relative pl-14 md:pl-20">
 <div class="absolute left-0 md:left-4 top-0 w-10 h-10 md:w-8 md:h-8 bg-brandBlue rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-white font-black text-base md:text-sm z-10">3</div>
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 pl-12 md:pl-0">Week 4-6: Prototype Development (OEM)</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">OEM: First articles, internal testing, design revisions</p>
 <p class="text-brandOrange text-sm mt-1 font-semibold">ODM: Skip to step 4</p>
 </div>
 
 <div class="relative pl-14 md:pl-20">
