 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Learning from others' experiences helps you avoid common pitfalls. Here are three brand journeys illustrating different manufacturing approaches.</p>
 
 <div class="space-y-8">
 <!-- Case Study 1 -->
 <div class="bg-white border-2 border-brandBlue rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
 <div class="bg-brandBlue p-6 text-white">
 <h3 class="text-lg font-black uppercase italic mb-2">Case Study: TechStart Electronics (ODM Success)</h3>
 <p class="text-white/70 text-sm">Startup: Launched with $15,000 budget in 8 weeks</p>
 </div>
 <div class="p-6">
 <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-6">
 <div class="text-center">
 <p class="text-3xl font-black text-brandBlue">$15K</p>
 <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs uppercase">Initial Investment</p>
 </div>
 <div class="text-center">
 <p class="text-3xl font-black text-brandBlue">8 Weeks</p>
 <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs uppercase">Time to Market</p>
 </div>
 <div class="text-center">
 <p class="text-3xl font-black text-brandBlue">500 Units</p>
 <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs uppercase">First Order</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">The Journey</h4>
 <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-4">TechStart wanted to launch a 3-in-1 wireless charger but had limited capital. They selected an ODM base from our catalog, customized with a unique matte black finish and premium packaging. They used Amazon FBA for fulfillment and achieved $45,000 in first-month sales.</p>
 <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Lessons Learned</h4>
 <ul class="text-slate-600 text-sm space-y-1">
 <li>, Started with ODM to validate market demand</li>
 <li>, Invested profits into custom tooling for v2 product</li>
 <li>, Used unique packaging to differentiate from competitors</li>
